More GUIDELINES from the NJ Department of Health:
There are four color-coded categories characterizing the risk of COVID-19 transmission in those regions . Green is low, yellow is moderate, orange is high, and red is very high. The levels will be posted on the state Health Department‚Äôs website "COVID-19 Weekly Activity Reports"
https://www.state.nj.us/health/cd/topics/ncov.shtml
*Salem is in the Southwest Region.

Region's that fall in the green, yellow, and orange categories will require students and staff to stay home when sick. When a region is in the red category, it is recommended they implement all-remote learning.

NJSIAA Return-to-Play Guidelines - Model 1 - Delayed Fall Season.
The official start of the fall sports season is being pushed back by approximately one month, with summer workouts for high school student-athletes ‚Äì which may begin on July 13 ‚Äì continuing until August 28. Following summer workouts (also known as the ‚Äúsummer recess period‚Äù), there will be a two-week hiatus from August 29 through September 13, during which only virtual meetings will be permitted, and only related to in-season (fall) sports. https://www.njsiaa.org/.

Dalton Peacock
June 12 at 4:32 AM ¬∑

Today was my graduation, and it was definetley one of those life changing things. Although it wasnt exactly how I imagined, It had the exact same impact and I am still thinking about it. Seing all of my past classmates and thinking to myself, "Wow. We all made it as a team. Even with COVID-19, even with the issues involving racism and the riots, we all got through the year." Class of 2020 isnt a class to be messed with. We are the BEST class. Thank you to everyone that has or will be giving me gifts, it is all much appreciated from the bottom of my heart!! Thank you Brandi Lee Peacock-Jenkins, Jeannie Peacock, Andy Peacock, Debbie Nelson, Lisa Nelson, Charles Heiser, Barbara Nelson and anyone else that has given me a roof, a hot meal and a loving home. I would not be the man I am today, or the student I was without the help of all of you.

shared_text:
Salem County Social updated their cover photo.
May 26, 2016 at 11:44 AM ¬∑

CELEBRATE FLAG DAY -JUNE 14TH
"Bernard Cigrand, a small-town Wisconsin teacher, originated the idea for an annual flag day, to be celebrated across the country every June 14, in 1885. That year, he led his school in the first formal observance of the holiday." - History Channel

"In 1916, President Woodrow Wilson issued a proclamation that officially established June 14 as Flag Day; on August 3, 1949, National Flag Day was established by an Act of Congress. Flag Day is not an official federal holiday. Title 36 of the United States Code, Subtitle I, Part A, CHAPTER 1, ¬ß 110[6] is the official statute on Flag Day; however, it is at the president's discretion to officially proclaim the observance. On June 14, 1937, Pennsylvania became the first U.S. state to celebrate Flag Day as a state holiday, beginning in the town of Rennerdale.[1] New York Statutes designate the second Sunday in June as Flag Day, a state holiday." - Wikipedia

STEAM: Summer Science at Home hosted by Rowan STEAM Academy. Salem students can register for the weeklong virtual camp being offered by Rowan University for students in the 7th-10th grade.

Students only have to register and enter the promo code instead of a form of payment. Funding provided by the Forman S. Acton Educational Foundation.

Prior to the start date, the Foundation will verify eligibility (Salem City resident or attending Salem City Schools).

Students will need a computer and wifi/internet capability to participate.

- $2 for 1 ticket, $10 for 6 tickets, $20 for 14 tickets.

SMS, 6th Grade Science Teacher, Melanie Nugent is coordinating "Goin' on a Bear Hunt", the goal is to flood the windows of households & shops with bears. She will then use it as a project with her students - observation, data collection, data analysis, communication, compare/contrast environment, and much more!

#randomactsofcommunity for the kids to enjoy when they are taking a walk or drive around their neighborhood with their family.

Based on the 1989 children's book We're Going on a Bear Hunt, by Michael Rosen. Communities across the country are putting teddy bears in their windows for the little ones to find.

Thanks for joining the fun by placing a stuffed bear in a window; communities around the nation are participating in bear hunts for the little ones to enjoy, while practicing social distancing! Please share with your FB friends!

shared_text:
Dr. Richard Warren Jr is with Kevin Taylor.
February 25 at 2:27 PM ¬∑

Another proud moment. Had the chance to return back to my high school to speak to the students. You could hear a pin drop in the room as they absorbed every word I spoke. I am certain that many of them will rise and achieve more than others expect. When you come from Salem , you are coming from a rich line of survivors with unmatched strength. Anything is possible. I came from the projects. Now I am a full time professor. Ram potential is limitless ‚ÄºÔ∏è #Ramproud #loveteaching #Hawkpride

April 1, 2020 is U.S. Census Day. A nationwide count of all U.S. residents occurs every 10 years and, starting in mid-March, households will receive a mailing inviting them to complete their census forms online. Census data is used for the following decade to determine New Jersey‚Äôs Congressional representation and the annual allocation of over $23 billion in federal funding to our state.
It's important!!!
And, the U.S. Census Bureau is looking to hire Census Takers. See the flyer for information on how you can become a Field Representative for the 2020 Census.

post_text:
SHS Alum, Richard H. Warren, Jr. will be returning to SHS this Friday, 2/14. Happy Valentine's Day!!!
Dr. Richard Warren Jr, is the 2019 Maryland State Teacher of the Year and a nationally awarded S.T.E.M innovator in Maryland. In fact, Samsung named him ‚Äúone of the leading solve for tomorrow teachers in the United States.‚Äù #rampride
shared_text:
Dr. Richard Warren Jr
April 1, 2019 at 6:04 PM ¬∑

CONFESSION...

Becoming a certified teacher was not easy for me. Although my pride will take a huge hit after this, I vow to be vulnerable.

I failed my praxis exams multiple times. I felt drained, defeated, and at times, helpless.

But I didn‚Äôt give up !

I thought about my students and how much they needed me to be their change agent . I thought about some of the hard times that I faced growing up and how they were dealing with some of those same things and needed an example of hope.

So I kept trying and passed those exams! I had know idea that all of accolades and accomplishments would be on the other side of the story. I was just a young man that wanted to see others become successful . 8 years later my heart remains the same.

Went back to my Alma Mater to share my story and give back 1k in scholarships ....

#Godsplan
#LoveTeaching
#VideoCreditSHS
